HEADWORD: Outmanoeuvre
<hw>Out`ma*noeu"vre</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To surpass, or get an advantage of,
in maneuvering; to outwit or frustrate by clever stratagems; to
outgeneral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

